Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.collection

Class EnumToIntMap<K extends Enum<K>>

java.lang.Object
nl.naturalis.common.collection.EnumToIntMap<K>
Type Parameters:
K - The type of the enum class
All Implemented Interfaces:
Emptyable
public final class EnumToIntMap<K extends Enum<K>> extends Object implements Emptyable
A fast enum-to-int map. The map is backed by a simple int array with the same length as the number of constants in the enum class. One integer must be designated to signify the absence of a key. By default, this is Integer.MIN_VALUE and, by default, all elements in the int array are set to this value (meaning the map is empty). It is not allowed to add a key with this value to the map, as is would in effect amount to removing that key from the map. It is also not allowed to pass this value to containsValue. In both cases an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. Empty enum classes (i.e. enum classes without enum constants) are not supported.
Author:
Ayco Holleman

      public EnumToIntMap(Class<K> enumClass, ToIntFunction<K> initializer)
      Creates a new EnumToIntMap using Integer.MIN_VALUE as the key-absent-value value and with its keys initialized using the specified initializer function. For example: 
      
 EnumToIntMap<DayOfWeek> map = new EnumToIntMap<>(DayOfWeek.class, k -> k.ordinal() + 1);
      Parameters:
      enumClass - The type of the enum class
      initializer - A function called to initialize the array elements
